(1, 5, 'The Big Oxmox advised her not to do so, because there were thousands of bad Commas, wild Question Marks and devious Semikoli, but the Little Blind Text didn’t listen. She packed her seven versalia, put her initial into the belt and made herself on the way.\nWhen she reached the first hills of the Italic Mountains, she had a last view back on the skyline of her hometown Bookmarksgrove, the headline of Alphabet Village and the subline of her own road, the Line Lane. Pityful a rethoric question ran over her cheek, then '),
(1, 6, 'Students or alumni of the National School of Decorative Arts of Paris or the School of the street madam, Ripoulin chose their name in reference to the famous Ripolin men but also to the word of verlan ripou (= rotten). Although they are often associated with graffiti since they took place in the streets (Paris, New York, in particular), the Ripoulin did not paint on the walls but on posters that they would then stick on them.'),
(1, 7, 'Founded in 2010, Birdy Kids now consists of two brothers, Guillaume and Gautier, gathered around a common project: a fun and colorful street art for everyone.\r\nFirst considered as a degradation of public space, Birdy is today recognized as one of the symbols of the city and is therefore spared by the maintenance services of the city.\r\nThe group participates in the promotion of street art in other cities, such as Paris or Barcelona.\r\nIn 2012, the collective is chosen as cultural ambassador for Lyon.'),
(1, 8, 'The Collectif Quatre Ailes is a group of artists who met in September 2002 to carry out the creation of multidisciplinary theatrical projects. Gathered around the same approach, these artists share a poetic imaginary, dreamlike, magical and have the ambition to combine multiple artistic disciplines to convey this imaginary. The Collective now consists of three active members: Michaël Dusautoy (director), Damien Saugeon (comedian and acrobat air) and Annabelle Brunet (visual artist, video artist). Until 2018 it was also composed of the actress Claire Corlier, associated with the Collective since its creation.'),
